                        data-module-name="utility-bar-module-print"></div></div></div></div></div><section id="module-position-OArYnSwmEfs" class="storytopbar-bucket leaderboard-ad-module"><div class="partner-placement asset-leaderboard-atf-ad leaderboard-ad" data-ad-placement="leaderboard_atf"></div></section><section id="module-position-OArYnSwh6Fs" class="storytopbar-bucket story-headline-module"><h1 class="asset-headline" itemprop="headline">US Trainers To Deploy To Ukraine</h1></section><section id="module-position-OArYnSwI-54" class="storytopbar-bucket story-byline-module"><div class="asset-metabar" itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person"><span itemprop="name" class="asset-metabar-author asset-metabar-item">
        By Paul McLeary
    </span><span class="asset-metabar-time asset-metabar-item nobyline">12:17 p.m. EST January 22, 2015</span></div></section><!-- p402_premium class is utilized by Google Consumer Surveys --><div class="asset-double-wide double-wide p402_premium" role="main" itemprop="articleBody"><div id="module-position-OArYnT5zhUI" class="story-asset story-leadin-asset"><h2 class="lead-in">Also Will Begin Shipment of US-funded Armored Vehicles</h2></div><div id="module-position-OArYnT5KINQ" class="story-asset story-metadata-asset"><div class="article-metadata-wrap"><section id="module-position-OArYnT40WSI" class="storymetadata-bucket expandable-photo-module"><aside itemprop="associatedMedia" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/ImageObject" class="single-photo expandable-collapsed"><div class="image-wrap"><img class="expand-img-vertical" itemprop="url" src="http://www.gannett-cdn.com/-mm-/d365966fc095dbad565adebecaec6de4d2900ab1/c=0-240-2832-4016&amp;r=537&amp;c=0-0-534-712/local/-/media/2015/01/21/DefenseNews/DefenseNews/635574536534245469-5988204096-998502ea11-o.jpg" alt="ukraine training" data-mycapture-src="http://www.gannett-cdn.com/media/2015/01/21/DefenseNews/DefenseNews/635574536534245469-5988204096-998502ea11-o.jpg" /><span class="toggle"></span><meta itemprop="name" content="ukraine training" /></div><p class="image-credit-wrap"><span class="js-caption-wrapper"><span class="cutline js-caption">US soldiers train with Ukrainian troops during Exercise Rapid Trident in 2011.</span><meta itemprop="copyrightHolder" content="" /><span class="credit">(Photo: Staff Sgt. Brendan Stephens/US Army)</span></span></p></aside></section></div></div><div id="module-position-OArYnT4wtt4" class="story-asset inline-share-tools-asset"><div class="inline-share-tools asset-inline-share-tools asset-inline-share-tools-top"><span
        class="inline-share-btn inline-share-btn-facebook"
        data-share-method="facebook"
        data-uotrack="InlineShareFacebookBtn"><span class="inline-share-count inline-share-count-facebook"></span><span class="inline-share-btn-label inline-share-btn-label-facebook">CONNECT</span></span><a
        class="inline-share-btn inline-share-btn-twitter"
        data-share-method="twitter"
        data-uotrack="InlineShareTwitterLink"
